A devastating blast at the Hilton hotel in Taba, Egypt's Red Sea resort, left over 100 dead or injured.
Another explosion was reported in the Sinai desert region of Nuaiba.
Israeli sources suspected a car bomb attack, contradicting initial reports of a gas leak.
Multiple blasts targeted tourists in the Sinai, with casualties including at least 23 Israelis.
Despite warnings, many Israelis continued to visit the popular Sinai resorts.
Israeli officials urged immediate evacuation following the attacks, emphasizing the persistent threat of terrorism in the region.
